v1.0.7: hold first action for the solver so the plan starts at step 1

If the solve hadn't finished by the time the first action fired (StepDelay
3.5s), greedy executed the opener and the plan — computed assuming a fresh
craft — then ran misaligned. Now the executor waits up to PlanGrace (12s) for
the plan before committing the first action, and only adopts a plan that
arrives while still at step 1; a late plan is discarded and greedy carries on.

